    "We note that this is often referred to as the \"macro-magnification\" because κ c and γ can be attributed to the lensing galaxy's macroscopic potential at the location of the multiple images.",
    "It can be seen from this equation that for positive parity images the magnification is always |μ| > 1.",
    "For negative parity the image can be magnified, |μ| > 1, or demagnified, |μ| < 1.",
    "The normalized lens equation Eq.",
    "(11) describes a mapping from the lens plane z to the source plane ζ."
